<concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="topic_3_5">
   <title>Filtering a Report by Additional Timeframes</title>
   <conbody>
    <p>After zooming into one timeframe as shown in the previous section, you can filter the report
      by an additional timeframe in the report filters area as shown below. </p>
    <fig><title>Figure 2-8: Report Filtering by Additional Timeframes</title>
    <image href="./media/Image_080.png" placement="break" scale="40" id="image_nh3_jcm_zx"/></fig>
     
    <p>You can further drill down into the data by removing values. To remove the values click the
      labels displaying the values to the right of the chart. The removed text values are displayed
      at the bottom of the chart. For example, in the screenshot below the hits on the site
        <codeph>http://www.slashdot.org</codeph> are removed. The green bar in the chart is also
      removed and the selected label to the right of the chart is also greyed out. This results list
      at the bottom of the report no longer display items containing the hyperlink
        <codeph>http://www.slashdot.org</codeph>.<note>Click a text area to display additional
        filters in the filter area of the report.</note></p>
    <fig><title>Figure 2-9: Report Drill-down</title><image href="./media/Image_081.png" placement="break" scale="40" id="image_oh3_jcm_zx"/></fig>
  </conbody>
</concept>
